You need two things: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` and a **custom back button** on the page.

### 1. Guard navigation in `AppShell.xaml.cs`

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    // Only intercept back navigation from EditProductPage
    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.CurrentPage.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();   // user chose "Stay" â€” cancel navigation

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

> **Key:** `GetDeferral()` is required because the confirmation is async. Without it, navigation completes before the dialog returns.

### 2. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage.xaml`

```xml
<ContentPage ...>
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding GoBackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

The `Command` triggers the same `GoToAsync("..")` flow, which fires `OnNavigating` and shows the guard:

```csharp
// In your ViewModel
[RelayCommand]
async Task GoBack()
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

### 3. Expose `HasUnsavedChanges` on the page

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }
}
```

Set this flag whenever a form field changes, and clear it after saving.

### How it all connects

- User taps **"Cancel"** â†’ `GoBackCommand` calls `GoToAsync("..")` â†’ `OnNavigating` fires with `ShellNavigationSource.Pop` â†’ dialog appears â†’ navigation is cancelled or allowed.
- User swipes/presses hardware back â†’ same `OnNavigating` guard runs automatically.
